## *Species Trends*

Models converged for five species/groups: Big Brown Bat (EPFU), Eastern Red Bat (LABO), Hoary Bat (LACI), Silver-haired Bat (LANO), and the combined Myotis group (40KMyo) (@fig-trends). Significant increases in nightly activity were detected for Big Brown Bat (β = 0.74, SE = 0.09, z = 8.11, p \< 0.001) and Eastern Red Bat (β = 0.81, SE = 0.10, z = 7.88, p \< 0.001). In contrast, no significant temporal trend was detected for Hoary Bat (β = 0.10, SE = 0.09, z = 1.10, p = 0.270), Silver-haired Bat (β = 0.06, SE = 0.13, z = 0.48, p = 0.633), or the combined Myotis group (β = 0.22, SE = 0.12, z = 1.81, p = 0.071).


