# Discussion

Data used for trends only uses autoID from Kaleidoscope, which has been shown to confuse Myotis spp. for LABO. so be careful here.

We could not use recordings from 2020-2021 and had to simply rely on the Alberta eBat resutls. This adds noise to the dataset since only the first 2 years use it. This might be the reason for the perceived increase in the species for EPFU and LABO.\
Results must be taken with caution because of small sample size, but overall can conclude that bat species at the grid cell are stable.

Keep in mind that in the winter of 2026 WNS has been confirmed across the rockies and most importantly in Cadamun cave. This just points to the importance of continues monitoring in the region.

